@node "amigaesp" "Amiga and Esperanto  "
There  are also some things related to Esperanto in Aminet.  The best way to get informed  about  the
existence of new and exciting Esperanto-related files is to perform a search on any Aminet mirrors out
there.

I personally recommend:

http://de.aminet.net                (Aminet Vollmirror in Germany)


Until now, these are the Esperanto related files I've found in Aminet:


(*) EsperantoAccen.lha dev/misc      3K    99  Esperanto.accent for translator.library
Esperanto.lha          misc/edu    448K   293  Introduct. to ESPERANTO w/ dictionaries
(*) EsperantoLang.lha  misc/misc     1K   112  Esperanto.language *NOW FIXED*
(*) LokaloRipari.lha   misc/misc     2K   111  Fixes EsperantaLokale.lha catalogs
(*) ISO3-Literoj.lha   text/font    35K   102  Some bitmap ISO-3 fonts (esperanto)
(*) Lat3CGTimes.lha    text/ifont   47K    98  CGTimes.type w/ Esperantist symbols
(*) EsperantoCX.lha    util/cdity   ??K    ??  This little piece of software ;))))
EsperantaLokal.lha     util/wb     167K   162  Locale catalogues in Esperanto & ISO Lat



Items marked with (*) were developed and uploaded to Aminet by me.


Future  projects  would  involve  more  fonts (bitmap and vector), Esperanto and ISO-3  compliant printer
drivers  (for  ASCII  printouts)  and  if  someone is interested  out  there  it  would  be nice to
create an Esperanto section in ATO (Amiga Translators' Organization) (http://ato.vapor.com/ato).


I  actually doesn't know Esperanto but I would like to learn...  I'll soon buy a lernolibro ;)
@endnode

